x4freetext: cross sections of Zn,Ga,Ge,As,and Se for 14.1 MeV
giving a 10.**8 n/cm2 flux (information from ARS,71).
-Made of natural elements of high purity (more than
6 cm3 Ge-Li detector,3.5 keV resolution for
Authors assumed a c.s. of 478.+-48. millibarns.
Mean neutron flux was (426.+-0.07) x 10**5 n/cm2/s.
The reaction c.s. was assumed to be 96.+-1. barns.
Relation between fast and slow fluxes was 11.6+-0.2.
The (n,p) cross section has been studied as a function
of the asymmetry parameter of the target nucleus for
each element and of the atomic number for the isotone
elements. Authors gave a method for predicting unknown
-Each cross section was measured 3 times, and the data
are the mean values of these three measurements.
-Data were corrected for neutron and gamma
self-absorption, and for (n,gamma) induced by slowed
Statistical error weighted by the inverse
of the standard deviation for each of the three
M.M. STATUS was added in Subentries.
Free text was corrected to be "human-readable".
SD: SF4 was corrected in REACTION code in
Subent 6. Ref. on ARS,71 moved to REL-REF
